The code in question looks like so:
  synchronized (overflowLock) {
    trimJob.setOffset(-1);
    trimJob.setRule(console.getSchedulingRule());
    trimJob.schedule();
  }

It looks like setRule(...) is called at a time when trimJob is expected to be a
new (not yet running) Job. However, the assertion failure is happening because
the job is actually running.

Looks like there's a synchronization problem here.
